Dear Sir:<br>
<br>
I am compelled to write after reading your response to one of the guildmembers of Midnight Sojourn in regards to Medicuus ninja looting the WW dragon neck piece.  I feel you are in error in your decision about this matter.<br>
<br>
Everquest is a great game, but it is poorly suited in many ways for multi group raiding parties (although the entire upper level game is designed around large, multi group raids).  There is no multi group communication channel, there is no shared exp between groups and there is no way to ensure that someone NOT in the group that got the kill message/exp will be properly awarded an item.<br>
<br>
In its wisdom, the makers of Everquest have set forth the following rules to project the players because of the above limitations to multi group raids.  These posted rules state:<br>
<br>
“Ninjalooting is defined as taking special equipment from a fallen creature without the express permission of those who killed the creature if they are in attendance.<br>
The purpose of this rule is to stop those who stand near creatures that carry special items and attempt loot that equipment prior to it being looted by the rightful owner.”<br>
<br>
I fail to see why you will not honor the rules which exist to protect us against situations EXACTLY like what happened to Midnight Sojourn.  Here is VERY clear case of inappropriate looting.  <br>
<br>
Please understand the terrible precedence you are setting and the rash of petitions and escalations that will occur if people who feel they can get away with ninjalooting begin to do so with increasing frequency.  What if the item was the epic drop of Ragefire?  What if some poor cleric had lost their pearl and all the work that goes into doing the cleric epic quest because it wasn’t announced that the cleric who spawned Ragefire would loot him?   What if it was a really nice drop from NToV?  What if it was a low level person on good giant faction hanging around and looting the head of King Tormax?<br>
<br>
Please tell me how we are supposed to implement your concept of “warning people that the corpse is not theirs to loot.”  Should it be a macro?  What is acceptable?  OOC, shout, say?  55+ corpses last 30 minutes, what if the random process takes a good bit of time, how often should we announce to the zone that the property of mob belongs to the group of individuals who actually killed the mob?  Every 5 minutes, every minute?  If you are insistent upon setting new policy in complete disregard of the current posted rules, please let us know how to proceed.<br>
<br>
I have to wonder if you are remotely familiar with the game of Everquest and the way multi group raids work to make such a decision.  Your decision has far reaching implications that will make it more difficult to ensure that the items dropped in multi group raids will be awarded to the appropriate individual.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
<br>
XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
<br>
Sometimes known as:<br>
Gloriana Frostglitter<br>
Oracle<br>
Erollisi Marr<br>
www.afflictionguild.com <br>
